org.xflatdb.xflat.query

Class IntervalSet<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.xflatdb.xflat.query.IntervalSet<T>

  • public class IntervalSet<T>
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents an immutable set of values defined in terms of several intervals. The set is the union of all the intervals.

      • between

        public static <U> IntervalSet<U> between(U lower,
                         U upper)
        Creates an IntervalSet representing all values between the two given values exclusive. That is, the interval (lower, upper)

        This is equivalent to gt(lower) ∩ lt(upper).

        Type Parameters:
        U -
        Parameters:
        lower - The exclusive lower bound of the interval set.
        upper - The inclusive upper bound of the interval set.
        Returns:
        the interval "(lower, upper)"

      • union

        public IntervalSet<T> union(IntervalSet<T> other,
                   java.util.Comparator<T> comparer)
        Gets the union of this IntervalSet with the other IntervalSet, using the given comparator. The returned interval set will contain the minimum number of Interval objects necessary to represent the union of this interval set with the other.

        The returned interval set is a new instance.

        Parameters:
        other - The other interval set with which to union this interval set.
        comparer - The comparator for begin and end values of the interval set.
        Returns:
        A new interval set containing the union.

      • intersection

        public IntervalSet<T> intersection(IntervalSet<T> other,
                          java.util.Comparator<T> comparer)
        Gets the intersection of this interval set with another interval set. The returned interval set will contain the minimum number of Interval objects necessary to represent the intersection of this interval set with the other.

        The returned interval set is a new instance.

        Parameters:
        other - The other interval set which has intersecting intervals.
        comparer - The comparer for values of the interval set.
        Returns:
        the intersection of this interval and the given interval.
